title: Saturday Road: OLH & West Alpine
description:
Classic Old La Honda & West Alpine

Weather looks great, but the northern Santa Cruz Mountains are hard to predict. Bring a layer

The route
- Saratoga maze to Foothill
- Left on El Monte
- Rest stop 1: Arastradero trailhead area
- Through Portola valley to OLH, regroup at the top on Skyline
- Descend W OLH, hard left on La Honda
    - Rest Stop 2: Park just up Sears Ranch past the store
- Down to left on Pescadero to W Alpine and redwoods and delightful climbing
- Restroom at the top just before Skyline
- Descend Page Mill to Moody to Summerhill to the golf course loop
- Then Foothill again to Stevens Canyon
- Rest stop 3: Right on Stevens Canyon before Mt Eden and first right
- Mt. Eden, right on Pierce, down 9, back to LG

**Sunday Group Ride Notice and Rules**

Join us for our Sunday group ride! Here are the key details and rules to ensure a pleasant ride for everyone:

1. **Being On Time**: It is essential to BE ON TIME! We will start the ride sharp at the set time.

2. **No Drop Social Ride**: This ride is a no-drop, social ride. The main group will maintain a pace and there will be a few regroup points during the ride (e.g., before complicate route with multiple turns or after a long climb.)

3. ** Experience Level**: The pace will be comfortable for advance beginner with climbing experience. Ensure you have the necessary experience and fitness to participate.

4. **Group Ride Etiquette**: Familiarize yourself with basic group ride hand signals and unwritten ethics.

5. **Route Knowledge**: If you decide to ride at a faster pace and get separated from the group, know the route and be prepared to find your own way home.

We look forward to enjoyable ride. See you on the road!
